{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place confectioners sugar, corn syrup, coconut oil, evaporated milk and peppermint extract into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 3.5<\/nobr>, then knead <nobr>30 sec\/<\/nobr>. Transfer dough to cling wrap and refrigerate 30 minutes. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place parchment on a clean work surface and dust with confectioners sugar. Transfer chilled dough to prepared parchment. Dust the top with confectioners sugar and roll out to ¼ inch thickness.","Cut out rounds with a cookie cutter (2 in.), reroll excess dough and repeat until all is used. Place rounds on parchment and slide onto a baking sheet. Freeze 10 minutes.","Place 12 oz bittersweet chocolate into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Melt <nobr>6 min\/120°F\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. With a candy thermometer, ensure temperature is between 115°F-120°F. If necessary heat a further <nobr>2-5 min\/120°F\/speed 2<\/nobr>, until chocolate temperature is within range.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, add 4 oz bittersweet chocolate and mix <nobr>2 min\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl.","Place water into mixing bowl and heat <nobr>20 min\/205°F\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Meanwhile continue tempering chocolate. Stir chocolate with spatula to cool to 83°F. Use a candy thermometer to ensure temperature is within range. Place the bowl of melted chocolate onto mixing bowl lid, over hot water and stir vigorously with spatula in 2-5 second bursts until temperature is between 88°F-91°F (see Tip).","With a fork, dip peppermint rounds into melted chocolate to coat. Shake off excess chocolate and place rounds on a clean piece of parchment. Refrigerate 10 minutes until set before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["16 oz confectioners sugar, plus extra to dust","2 oz corn syrup","1 ½ oz coconut oil","1 ½ oz evaporated milk","¼ tsp peppermint extract","16 oz bittersweet chocolate, broken in pieces, divided","20 oz water,"]}],"id":"r411308","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-kktN9zQT7Cc\/XZWdf5yT-QI\/AAAAAAAAemU\/swWnnh8E1QUfjBixTbgbGXteXcAk89wdACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_HQQ7rN8fqeb_7wlP.png","title":"Chocolate Peppermint Bites","publishedAt":"2018-10-19T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2 g","fat":"9 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"21 g","calories":"732 kJ \/ 175 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling wrap, parchment paper, rolling pin, baking sheet, cookie cutter (2 in.), candy thermometer, refrigerator, freezer","hintsAndTricks":["To garnish with a ribbon look: drizzle tempered chocolate onto bites just before chocolate sets.","When dipping candies: use a candy thermometer to check temperature of melted chocolate is maintained at 88°F-91°F for proper setting. Place the bowl with melted chocolate on mixing bowl lid and stir with spatula for 2-5 seconds, as needed, to keep chocolate tempered.","For best results: look for chocolate with high cocoa solids. Cocoa or some derivative, such as cocoa butter should be the primary ingredient. Quality chocolate will have a matte gloss finish and smooth texture that is free of discoloration. Dark chocolate should make a snapping sound when broken without crumbling while white and milk chocolate should bend rather than snap."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","40m","30 pieces"]}